  "translations": {
    "en": "O slaves of Allah! There is no escape from death, so beware of it before it occurs and be prepared. You are being hunted by death; if you stop, it will capture you, and if you flee, it will find you. Its company is more constant than your own shadow! It is tied to your forelocks, and life on earth is being folded from behind you. So remember death frequently, especially when your mind fights you for temptations, for death is a sufficient admonisher. And the Prophet, peace be upon him and his progeny, often reminded his companions to remember death, saying: Remember death often, for it demolishes all pleasures and is a barrier between you and your base desires.",
    "ur": "O slaves of Allah! There is no escape from death, so beware of it before it occurs and be prepared. You are being hunted by death; if you stop, it will capture you, and if you flee, it will find you. Its company is more constant than your own shadow! It is tied to your forelocks, and life on earth is being folded from behind you. So remember death frequently, especially when your mind fights you for temptations, for death is a sufficient admonisher. And the Prophet, peace be upon him and his progeny, often reminded his companions to remember death, saying: Remember death often, for it demolishes all pleasures and is a barrier between you and your base desires.",
